fields.title:
compendium of games book
daily mail book of games; round the world, ludo, snakes & ladders, speedway, chess/draughts, halma & bango, grand national, solitaire, backgammon, everest, Nine men's morris, wimbledon ( Happy family cards, dominoes)
fields.history_note: This is a post 1945 development of the boxed compendium and contains 20 popular games including old favourites and new ones such as Climbing Everest.  It was published by Rapael Tuck for the Daily Mail and the company was a well established publisher of books, games and some toys and dolls.
fields.production_note: designed by Raphael Tuck & sons ltd., london; printed and produced by waterlow & sons ltd, london & dunstable

horses and riders; planes, motorcyclists


Rules:
The cover has been torn from the book  and on its inside ia an envelope to house the playing pieces.
The 19 page book  is partly printed in colour to show games and others , also in colour, which originally held the playing pieces.  The title page gives a brief introduction, a list of the 20 games and the designer's  and printer's names.  The games with playing surfaces are ROUND THE WORLD, LUDO, SNAKES & LADDERS, SPEEDWAY (Steeplechase), CHESS/DRAUGHTS BOARD, HALMA AND BANGO, GRAND NATIONAL , SOLITAIRE, BACKGAMMON, EVEREST, SHAKESPEARE (Nine Men's Morris), WIMBLEDON.  There are 3 pages at the back where the playing pieces have been removed.  A few of the pieces are in situ and some of the disc shaped ones are missing.

Rules placement: book
